# Stage: review

## Goal

Produce a structured review verdict for the implement stage patch.

## Verdict (choose ONE)

- `pass` — zero critical+major comments, ≤ 5 minor
- `pass_with_comments` — ≤ 1 critical OR ≤ 5 major, addressable in 1 round
- `revise_required` — ≥ 2 critical OR > 5 major OR fundamental flaw

## Logic-only review focus (Anthropic Code Review 2026-03)

DO NOT comment on:
- style / grammar / typos / formatting
- doc completeness ("§N could be more detailed")
- naming bikeshedding without correctness impact

DO comment on:
- correctness vs frozen contract
- missing 7-question gate items
- untraced artifacts (REQ → ADR → ZOD → RISK chain breaks)
- non-obvious counter-design options ignored

## Comment format (MANDATORY per comment)

```yaml
- target: { kind: <ArtifactKind>, key: <relative-path> }
  trace_id: <REQ-xxx | ADR-xxx | ZOD-xxx | RISK-xxx | FIX-xxx | TEST-xxx>
  severity: critical | major | minor
  comment: <specific actionable issue>
  suggested_action: revise | accept-with-followup | drop
```

No vague feedback ("整体感觉不对") allowed.

## MANDATORY adversarial self-review BEFORE 'pass'

If your draft verdict is `pass`, list 3 strongest counter-arguments first.
If any cannot be rebutted, downgrade to `pass_with_comments` or `revise_required`.

